        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 10 at 8:46PM MDT by NWS Great Falls MT</headline>
        <description>At 845 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 8
miles southeast of Valier, or 8 miles northwest of Conrad, moving
southeast at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor hail damage to vegetation is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Conrad and Ledger.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
